text: Eugenie Bouchard (born February 25, 1994) is a Canadian professional tennis player. She was born in Montreal, Quebec.WTA profile She lives in Miami Beach, Florida. Bouchard turned professional in 2009. She was the losing finalist at the 2014 Wimbledon Championships. Her world ranking peaked at no.5 later that year. == References == Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Canadian tennis players Category:Female tennis players Category:Sportspeople from Montreal Category:Twin people from Canada
